---
import MarketingLayout from "@/layouts/MarketingLayout.astro";
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Tailory"
  description="Tailory's privacy policy. The short version: we never see your data. Your resume stays on your device."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-8 pb-12 pt-24">
    <p class="mb-6 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[#a0b8ab]">Privacy</p>
    <h1
      class="max-w-2xl leading-[1.1] text-[#0e2418]"
      style="font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(36px, 4.5vw, 56px); font-weight: 700"
    >
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-8 h-px w-20 bg-[#ccddd4]"></div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-8 pb-24">
    <!-- Short version callout -->
    <div class="mb-12 rounded-xl border border-[#1d6648]/30 bg-[#1d6648]/5 px-8 py-6">
      <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#0e2418]">
        Tailory never sees your data. Your resume stays on your device.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- What we collect -->
    <div class="mb-12 border-t border-[#ccddd4] pt-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-[#0e2418]" style="font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif">
        What we collect
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
        Nothing. Tailory does not collect any personal data. There are no analytics, no tracking
        cookies, no form submissions, and no logging of any kind. We have no user accounts and no
        database.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- How your data is stored -->
    <div class="mb-12 border-t border-[#ccddd4] pt-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-[#0e2418]" style="font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif">
        How your data is stored
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
        When you edit your resume in Tailory, the data is saved to your browser's IndexedDB — a
        local storage mechanism built into every modern browser. This storage:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[#1d6648]">→</span>
          <span>Lives entirely on your device. It never leaves your browser.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[#1d6648]">→</span>
          <span>Persists across browser sessions until you clear your browser data.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[#1d6648]">→</span>
          <span>Is only accessible to the Tailory page — other sites cannot read it.</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[#1d6648]">→</span>
          <span>Can be deleted at any time by clearing your browser's site data.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Third-party services -->
    <div class="mb-12 border-t border-[#ccddd4] pt-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-[#0e2418]" style="font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif">
        Third-party services
      </h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
        Tailory uses two external services:
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#ccddd4] bg-white px-5 py-4">
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-[#0e2418]">Google Fonts</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
            The Lora and DM Sans typefaces are loaded from Google Fonts on page load. Google may log
            this request per their own privacy policy. If this concerns you, you can self-host
            Tailory and serve the fonts locally.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-[#ccddd4] bg-white px-5 py-4">
          <p class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-[#0e2418]">GitHub Pages / Vercel</p>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
            Tailory's static files are hosted on a static hosting platform. The host may log
            standard HTTP request metadata (IP address, user agent, timestamp) as part of normal
            server operation. No resume content is ever transmitted.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <div class="mb-12 border-t border-[#ccddd4] pt-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-bold text-[#0e2418]" style="font-family: 'Lora', Georgia, serif">
        Contact
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-[#3d6650]">
        If you have any questions about this policy, please{" "}
        <a
          href="https://github.com/abijith-suresh/tailory/issues"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          class="text-[#1d6648] underline underline-offset-2 hover:no-underline"
        >
          open an issue on GitHub
        </a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Effective date -->
    <div class="border-t border-[#ccddd4] pt-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-[#a0b8ab]">Effective date: January 2025</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
